  "texts": [
    "The basic components of the '2S_DenseViT ' model consist of obtaining feature maps from the Dense-Net-201 and MaxViT models.",
    "The DenseNet-201 model uses its feature layers and adds a MaxPool2d layer to decrease the spatial dimensions.",
    "Similarly, MaxViT utilizes its feature extraction layers in its model.",
    "The purpose of these extracted feature blocks is to gather a wide range of varied and detailed representations from the input data.To further analyze and manipulate these characteristics, two more classifiers are included.",
    "After extracting the features from DenseNet-201 model we used pooling operation with AdaptiveAvgPool2d, followed by a flattening operation and a linear layer that produces log probabilities in a lower dimensional space."
  ],
